                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5315/926.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Reid</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Knox says that the proposed terms as reported in Mr. Reid’s telegram of May
                    18 are acceptable to this Government if the other Governments agree. Adds that
                    the New York group also concurs. Directs that telegram of May 18 and this reply
                    be repeated to Paris and Berlin.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
